.TH ZOPEN-QUERY "1" "June 2026" "zopen tools 0.8.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zopen-query \- manual page for zopen-query 0.8.5
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zopen-query
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR] [\fI\,VERB\/\fR] [\fI\,PACKAGE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
zopen\-query \-  a utility for zopen community to query packages and repos.
.IP
VERB is the action to take, which is one of
.HP
\fB\-\-list\fR, \fB\-\-remote\-search\fR, \fB\-\-installed\fR
.IP
PACKAGE is a package, specified for \fB\-\-remote\-search\fR
.SS "Verbs:"
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-installed\fR
list installed zopen community.
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fR
list all available zopen community.
.TP
\fB\-\-remote\-search\fR
regex match package against available zopen community
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-details\fR
include full details for listings.
.HP
\fB\-\-category\fR <category> apply a category filter.
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
print this help
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-header\fR,
suppress the header for the output.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-version\fR,
suppress version information, return package names.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR
run in verbose mode.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
print version
.PP
